The hash value is an integer that uniquely represents the tuple

> Problem: Read an integer n representing the number of elements, then read n space-separated integers, store them in a tuple t, and print the hash value of the tuple using the hash() function.

  > Solution:

if __name__ == '__main__':
    n = int(raw_input())
    t = tuple(map(int, raw_input().split()))
    
    print(hash(t))
